.\" Manpage for wt — Git Worktree Manager
.TH WT 1 "2025" "wt 1.0.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
wt \- minimal Git worktree manager with auto-cd support

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wt
.I command
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wt
is a thin wrapper around
.BR git-worktree (1)
that enforces a consistent directory layout, sanitizes branch names,
auto-registers an ignore rule, and \(em when the shell function is
installed \(em automatically changes the current directory after
worktree operations.

All linked worktrees are placed under:

.RS
.I <repo-root>/.worktree/<repo-name>.<sanitized-branch>
.RE

For example, branch
.B feature/login
in a repo called
.B myapp
produces:

.RS
.I .worktree/myapp.feature-login
.RE

.B wt
works from any directory inside the repository, including from within
a linked worktree or from the
.I .worktree/
container directory itself.

.SH SHELL SETUP
.B wt
cannot change the directory of the calling shell on its own.  Install
the shell wrapper by adding the following line to
.B ~/.bashrc
or
.BR ~/.zshrc :

.RS
.EX
eval "$(wt init)"
.EE
.RE

This defines a shell function named
.B wt
that calls the binary once and performs any
.BR cd (1)
operations that the binary requests.  The function is compatible with
both
.BR bash (1)
and
.BR zsh (1).

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B init
Print the shell function definition to standard output.  Intended for:
.EX
    eval "$(wt init)"
.EE

.TP
.BI add " branch"
Create a new linked worktree for
.IR branch .
If the branch does not exist locally it is created.  If the worktree
already exists, the command is a no-op and the shell wrapper cds into
the existing path.

.TP
.BR rm \ [\fB-f\fR]\ [\fIbranch\fR]
Remove a linked worktree.

Without arguments, removes the worktree the shell is currently inside
and returns to the main worktree root.

With a
.I branch
argument, removes that specific worktree regardless of the current
directory.  The argument is resolved by scanning the
.I .worktree/
directory on disk, so it is immune to remote-URL or directory renames.

.B -f / --force
is passed through to
.BR git-worktree-remove (1)
to allow removal of a worktree with uncommitted changes.

When removing the worktree currently occupied by the shell,
.B wt
changes the process working directory to the main repository root
before invoking git, ensuring compatibility with git versions that
refuse to remove a worktree whose path contains the process CWD.

.TP
.BI co " branch"
.PD 0
.TP
.BI checkout " branch"
.PD
Change directory into the worktree for
.IR branch .
The worktree must already exist; use
.B wt add
to create it first.

.TP
.BR ls
.PD 0
.TP
.BR list
.PD
Display all worktrees.  The currently active worktree is marked with
a
.B ▶
arrow and highlighted.  Each entry shows the directory name, the
abbreviated HEAD commit SHA, and the branch name.  The
.B [main]
badge appears at the end of each main-worktree line so the SHA and
branch columns stay aligned across all rows.

Names longer than 50 characters are truncated with an ellipsis.

.TP
.BI mv " from to"
.PD 0
.TP
.BI move " from to"
.PD
Move (rename) the worktree identified by
.I from
to the path derived from
.IR to .
The destination uses the same name prefix as the source directory,
keeping worktree names consistent even if
.BR repo_name ()
would return a different value today.

If the shell is currently inside the source worktree it will be
redirected to the new path automatically.

.TP
.B prune
Run
.B git worktree prune
to remove stale administrative files for worktrees that no longer
exist on disk.

.TP
.BR nuke \ [\fB-f\fR]
Remove
.I all
linked worktrees and delete each worktree's associated local branch.
Prompts for confirmation unless
.B -f / --force
is given.  The shell is returned to the main worktree root if it was
inside any of the removed worktrees.

.SH BRANCH SANITIZATION
Branch names may contain characters that are not safe as directory
components.
.B wt
applies the following transformations to derive a directory name:

.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B /
is replaced by
.B -
.IP \(bu 2
Any character that is not alphanumeric, a dot, a hyphen, or an
underscore is replaced by
.B -
.IP \(bu 2
Leading and trailing hyphens are stripped.
.IP \(bu 2
Consecutive hyphens are collapsed to a single hyphen.
.RE

.SH WORKTREE RESOLUTION
When resolving a user-supplied branch or worktree name for
.BR rm ,
.BR co ,
and
.BR mv ,
.B wt
scans the
.I .worktree/
directory on disk and matches by sanitized suffix.  This approach is
immune to prefix mismatches that could occur if the repository was
renamed, moved, or the origin remote URL changed after worktrees were
first created.

.SH IGNORE RULE
The first time a worktree is added,
.B wt
appends
.B /.worktree
to
.I .git/info/exclude
so that the directory is invisible to
.BR git-status (1)
without modifying any tracked file.

.SH COLORS
Output is colorized when
.B TERM
is set to a non-dumb value.  Colors are disabled when:

.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B NO_COLOR
is set to any non-empty value (https://no-color.org)
.IP \(bu 2
.B TERM
is
.B dumb
or unset
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable ANSI color output when set to any non-empty value.
.TP
.B TERM
Used to detect whether color output is appropriate.

.SH FILES
.TP
.I <repo-root>/.worktree/
Directory that holds all linked worktrees managed by
.BR wt .
.TP
.I <repo-root>/.git/info/exclude
Receives the
.B /.worktree
entry on first use.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
A usage error, a missing worktree, or an underlying
.BR git (1)
failure occurred.  A diagnostic message is written to standard error.

.SH EXAMPLES

.SS One-time setup
.EX
echo 'eval "$(wt init)"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc
.EE

.SS Daily workflow
.EX
# Start work on a new feature (works from anywhere in the repo)
wt add feature/payments
# → creates .worktree/myrepo.feature-payments, cd's into it

# List all worktrees
wt ls

# Jump to an existing worktree
wt co feature/payments

# Rename a worktree
wt mv feature/payments feature/stripe-payments

# Remove — works even when you're inside the worktree
wt rm              # removes current worktree, cd's to repo root
wt rm feature/old  # removes by branch name (with slash) or short name

# Tear down everything
wt nuke -f
.EE

.SH TESTING
A test suite ships alongside the binary:

.EX
bash wt_test.sh [path/to/wt]
WT_BIN=/usr/local/bin/wt bash wt_test.sh
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-worktree (1),
.BR git (1)

.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/your-org/wt/issues

